OL,6,FPerpetrators could be subjected to
OL,7,Ftagging or behaviour change programmes
OL,8,Funder the stronger, more flexible
OL,9,Fmeasures and those who breach the
OL,10,Forders could face up to five years in
OL,11,Fprison.
OL,13,FThe Government has previously said the
OL,14,Fmeasures will be rolled out nationwide
OL,15,Fbut no date has been given.
OL,17,FNearly #2 million will also be
OL,18,Finvested into a network of officers to
OL,19,Ftarget violence against women and
OL,20,Fgirls online.
